race.comment: The $250,000 Maiden Plate kicks us off. MISTY VEIL (9) is unlucky to still be a maiden hitting the frame in all three starts to date and will be ready to peak now third run back from a spell. Has been given a bit of a tune-up trial at Rosehill in preparation for this and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. ZOUFAME (5) just ran into one better at Bathurst on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Revved up for this with two recent trials and the stable has been on fire of late. Has to be included in calculations. QUICKZOU (7) gets the reliable Gollan/Maloney combination and shouldn't be discounted lightly. The well-related BUCKEYE (2) (full to G3 winner Amelita) has placed two of three when fresh and may run a race first-up. SCRUMPTIOUS (10) rounds out the selections in an open race.
